@baseUrl = http://localhost:3000

### 1. Public — list all products
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/products

###

### 2. Signup admin
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/signup
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "admin@test.com",
  "password": "admin123",
  "role": "admin"
}

###

### 3. Signup regular user
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/signup
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "user@test.com",
  "password": "user123"
}

###

### 4. Login as admin (sets HTTP-only cookie)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "admin@test.com",
  "password": "admin123"
}

###

### 5. Get current user (requires login cookie)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/me

###

### 6. Get single product (requires login cookie)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/products/1

###

### 7. Create product — admin only (requires admin login cookie)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/products
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Monitor",
  "price": 400
}

###

### 8. Login as regular user
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "user@test.com",
  "password": "user123"
}

###

### 9. Create product as user — should return 403
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/products
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Denied Product",
  "price": 1
}

###

### 10. Logout
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/logout

###

### 11. Me after logout — should return 401
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/me

###
